<h4 id="definition">Definition</h4>
<p>\(\mathrm{B}(x, y)=\int_{0}^{1} t^{x-1}(1-t)^{y-1} d t\) <br /></p>
<ul>
  <li>the beta function, also called the Euler integral of the first kind.</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="properties">Properties</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Symmetry: B(x,y)=B(y,x)</li>
  <li>Relationship between gamma function and beta function: \(\mathrm{B}(x, y)=\frac{\Gamma(x) \Gamma(y)}{\Gamma(x+y)}\)</li>
  <li>when x and y are positive integers: \(\mathrm{B}(x, y)=\frac{(x-1) !(y-1) !}{(x+y-1) !}\)</li>
</ol>
